Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Halve and peel @Yellow Onion{1}; mince one half (whole onion for 4). Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}.

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}(to taste). (For 4 servings, spread potatoes out across entire sheet; roast ~{20-25%minutes} total.)

Roast on top rack for ~{10%minutes} (you'll add the green beans then).

Once potatoes have roasted 10 minutes, remove sheet from oven. Carefully toss @Green Beans{6%ounce} on empty side with a drizzle of @olive oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}(to taste). (For 4 servings, leave potatoes roasting and add green beans to a second baking sheet; roast on middle rack.)

Return to top rack until potatoes are golden brown and green beans are tender, ~{10-15%minutes} more.

== Pork Chops ==

While veggies roast, pat @Pork Chops{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{}, then coat with as much @Bold & Savory Steak Spice{1%tablespoon} as will stick.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a large #pan over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

> TIP: If crust begins to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

Turn off heat; transfer pork to a #plate. Wipe out pan.

== Creamy Pan Sauce ==

Heat another drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in same pan over medium heat. Add minced onion; cook, stirring, until softened and lightly browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in @Beef Stock Concentrate{1} and @water{1/4%cup} (1/3 cup for 4 servings). Bring to a simmer and cook until reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}. Season generously with @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Toss green beans with lemon zest.

Divide pork, potatoes, and green beans between plates. Spoon sauce over pork. Serve with lemon wedges on the side.